"England":"England"},"cs":{"about 1225–1283":"okolo 1225–1283","1189–1248":"1189–1248","1225–1283":"1225–1283","–Male":"Zesnulý","1225–Female":"1225–Zesnulá","1246–1297":"1246–1297","1248–1298":"1248–1298","1250–1300":"1250–1300","1158–1230":"1158–1230","–Female":"Zesnulá","about 1250":"okolo 1250","1297":"1297","1230":"1230","1283":"1283","1250":"1250","1248":"1248","1225":"1225","1158":"1158","1246":"1246","1300":"1300","about 1248":"okolo 1248","1189":"1189","1298":"1298","about 1246":"okolo 1246","about 1225":"okolo 1225","about 1245":"okolo 1245","about 1188":"okolo 1188","about 1230":"okolo 1230","Bradenlove, Buckinghamshire, England":"Buckinghamshire, Anglie, United Kingdom","West Horsley, Surrey, England":"West Horsley, Surrey, Anglie","Stanwell, Middlesex, England":"Stanwell, Middlesex, Anglie, United Kingdom","England":"Anglie"},"da":{"about 1225–1283":"omkring 1225–1283","1189–1248":"1189–1248","1225–1283":"1225–1283","–Male":"Afdød","1225–Female":"1225–Afdød","1246–1297":"1246–1297","1248–1298":"1248–1298","1250–1300":"1250–1300","1158–1230":"1158–1230","–Female":"Afdød","about 1250":"omkring 1250","1297":"1297","1230":"1230","1283":"1283","1250":"1250","1248":"1248","1225":"1225","1158":"1158","1246":"1246","1300":"1300","about 1248":"omkring 1248","1189":"1189","1298":"1298","about 1246":"omkring 1246","about 1225":"omkring 1225","about 1245":"omkring 1245","about 1188":"omkring 1188","about 1230":"omkring 1230","Bradenlove, Buckinghamshire, England":"Buckinghamshire, England, United Kingdom","West Horsley, Surrey, England":"West Horsley, Surrey, England","Stanwell, Middlesex, England":"Stanwell, Middlesex, England, United Kingdom","England":"England"},"nl":{"about 1225–1283":"circa 1225–1283","1189–1248":"1189–1248","1225–1283":"1225–1283","–Male":"Overleden","1225–Female":"1225–Overleden","1246–1297":"1246–1297","1248–1298":"1248–1298","1250–1300":"1250–1300","1158–1230":"1158–1230","–Female":"Overleden","about 1250":"circa 1250","1297":"1297","1230":"1230","1283":"1283","1250":"1250","1248":"1248","1225":"1225","1158":"1158","1246":"1246","1300":"1300","about 1248":"circa 1248","1189":"1189","1298":"1298","about 1246":"circa 1246","about 1225":"circa 1225","about 1245":"circa 1245","about 1188":"circa 1188","about 1230":"circa 1230","Bradenlove, Buckinghamshire, England":"Buckinghamshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","West Horsley, Surrey, England":"West Horsley, Surrey, England","Stanwell, Middlesex, England":"Stanwell, Middlesex, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","England":"England"},"en":{"about 1225–1283":"about 1225–1283","1189–1248":"1189–1248","1225–1283":"1225–1283","–Male":"Deceased","1225–Female":"1225–Deceased","1246–1297":"1246–1297","1248–1298":"1248–1298","1250–1300":"1250–1300","1158–1230":"1158–1230","–Female":"Deceased","about 1250":"about 1250","1297":"1297","1230":"1230","1283":"1283","1250":"1250","1248":"1248","1225":"1225","1158":"1158","1246":"1246","1300":"1300","about 1248":"about 1248","1189":"1189","1298":"1298","about 1246":"about 1246","about 1225":"about 1225","about 1245":"about 1245","about 1188":"about 1188","about 1230":"about 1230","Bradenlove, Buckinghamshire, England":"Buckinghamshire, England, United Kingdom","West Horsley, Surrey, England":"West Horsley, Surrey, England","Stanwell, Middlesex, England":"Stanwell, Middlesex, England, United Kingdom","England":"England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Windsor","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English:","habitational name from Windsor (Berkshire), Windsor in Stratford upon Avon (Warwickshire), Winsor in Copythorne (Hampshire), Winsor in Yealmpton (Devon), or Broadwindsor and Little Windsor (Dorset). All these places have the same linguistic origin, whose meaning is controversial, but seems to be ‘windlass bank’ (Old English <i>windels</i> + <i>ōra</i>).","in Yorkshire perhaps a habitational name from Winds Over in Middleton (near Ilkley, Yorkshire). The placename probably derives from Old English <i>wind</i> ‘wind’ (genitive <i>windes</i>) + <i>ofer</i> ‘slope, hill, ridge’."],"variants":[{"name":"Winzer","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Gerhard, Ilse, Ingo, Wilhelm.","German: occupational name for a vine-grower or vintner, Middle High German <i>winzer</i>.","German: habitational name from any of various places so named in Bavaria."]},{"name":"Winsor","meanings":["English: variant of   Windsor  . This is the spelling used for places so named in Devon and Hampshire.","Perhaps also an Americanized form of German   Winzer  ."]}]},{"name":"Hugh","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old French name, <i>Hugues</i>, <i>Hugo</i>, of Germanic (Frankish) origin, derived from <i>hug</i> ‘heart, mind, spirit’. It was originally a short form of various compound names containing this element. This was borne by the aristocracy of medieval France, adopted by the Normans, and introduced by them to Britain. It was consistently one of the most popular boys' names in the Middle Ages in England, but fell out of favour in the 16th century until it was revived in the 20th century. Little Hugh of Lincoln was a child supposed in the Middle Ages to have been murdered by Jews in about  1255 , a legend responsible for several outbursts of anti-Semitism at various times. The story is referred to by  Chaucer  in The Prioress's Tale. He is not to be confused with  St Hugh of Lincoln  (  1140–1200 ), bishop of Lincoln (  1186–1200 ), who was noted for his charity and good works, his piety, and his defence of the Church against the State. Since the later Middle Ages <i>Hugh</i> has also been used as an Anglicized form of the Gaelic name Aodh ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Hugh de Windsor was born about 1225, in West Horsley, Surrey, England, United Kingdom as the son of William de Windsor III and Edyth Moses. He married Godeholde de St John about 1245, in England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 3 daughters. He died in 1283, in Buckinghamshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 59."},"et":{"about 1225–1283":"umbes 1225–1283","1189–1248":"1189–1248","1225–1283":"1225–1283","–Male":"Surnud","1225–Female":"1225–Surnud","1246–1297":"1246–1297","1248–1298":"1248–1298","1250–1300":"1250–1300","1158–1230":"1158–1230","–Female":"Surnud","about 1250":"umbes 1250","1297":"1297","1230":"1230","1283":"1283","1250":"1250","1248":"1248","1225":"1225","1158":"1158","1246":"1246","1300":"1300","about 1248":"umbes 1248","1189":"1189","1298":"1298","about 1246":"umbes 1246","about 1225":"umbes 1225","about 1245":"umbes 1245","about 1188":"umbes 1188","about 1230":"umbes 1230","Bradenlove, Buckinghamshire, England":"Buckinghamshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","West Horsley, Surrey, England":"West Horsley, Surrey, England","Stanwell, Middlesex, England":"Stanwell, Middlesex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"England"},"fi":{"about 1225–1283":"noin 1225–1283","1189–1248":"1189–1248","1225–1283":"1225–1283","–Male":"Kuollut","1225–Female":"1225–Kuollut","1246–1297":"1246–1297","1248–1298":"1248–1298","1250–1300":"1250–1300","1158–1230":"1158–1230","–Female":"Kuollut","about 1250":"noin 1250","1297":"1297","1230":"123